{"title_page": "Alessio Bidoli", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|reason=Persistent [[WP:Disruptive editing|disruptive editing]]|small=yes}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{COI|date=April 2020}}\n{{Notability|Music|date=April 2020}}\n{{advert|date=October 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name        = Alessio Bidoli\n| image = Alessio Bidoli e Bruno Canino (Ivrea SMC records studio).jpg\n| alt       = \n| caption      = \n| image_size     = \n| background     = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name     = \n| alias       = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|08|18}}\n| birth_place    = \n| death_date     = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|1986|08|18}} (death date then birth) -->\n| origin       = \n| instrument     = Violin\n| genre       = [[Classical music|Classical]]\n| occupation     = \n| years_active    = \n| label       = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website      = {{url|http://www.alessiobidoli.com}}\n}}\n'''Alessio Bidoli''' (born 1986) is a Italian violinist.  <ref>https://www.7giorni.info/cultura/peschiera-borromeo/il-talento-peschierese-alessio-bidoli-si-esibira-al-teatro-cinema-de-sica.html</ref>\n\n==Biography==\n\n===Musical education===\nShe was introduced to music with piano studies at age 6; in the following years, he began studying the violin. Even in the early years, he began to perform publicly as a soloist, participating in and winning numerous national competitions. <ref>https://www.universalmusic.it/musica-classica/artista/alessio-bidoli_33761664456/ </ref> At age 21, she was admitted at the Haute Ecole de Musique de Lausanne and Mozarteum (Salzburg) under Pierre Amoyal , and then the [[Accademia Musicale Chigiana]] in Siena, where she was trained by Master [[Salvatore Accardo]].<ref>http://www.mitosettembremusica.it/sites/default/files/2019-05/30_alessio_bidoli_san_fedele_scheda_web_print.pdf</ref>\nAt age 20, he graduated from the Verdi Conservatory in [[Milan]] with highest marks and honors. He then received a specialization diploma for violin from the International Piano Academy \"Incontri col Maestro\" in Imola.<ref>https://www.mywhere.it/70627/alessio-bidoli-chamber-works-nino-rota.html</ref>\n\n===Career===\n\n\nHe performed and collaborated with international musicians such as [[Bruno Canino]], [[Pierre Amoyal]], Irene Veneziano,Massimo Mercelli and many others. <ref>https://open.spotify.com/artist/1ojJIJOWiOBM7BS2gAc3Ld</ref>\nHe has featured with [[Vittorio Sgarbi]] in the theatre project Il Fin la Maraviglia, an account of the Baroque age via images and sounds, which was performed at the theatre in Chiasso (Switzerland) in 2015.<ref>https://luganoeventi.ch/it/eventi/25985/il-fin-la-maraviglia</ref>\nIn April 2009, he was struck down by a viral infection that led to his becoming tetraplegic, arising from Guillain-Barr\u00e9 Syndrome, but he succeeded in playing the violin again two years later, despite his medical prognosis<ref>https://www.corriere.it/buone-notizie/cards/natale-neurochirurgo-italiano-che-salva-bambini-kirgizi-5-storie-corriere/alessio-violino-nonno_principale.shtml</ref>\nBidoli has appeared as guest artist in radio broadcasts on Radio France, NDR Kultur, Radio Svizzera Italiana, RAI Radio 3<ref>https://www.raiplayradio.it/audio/2018/11/PRIMO--MOVIMENTO-5662aef6-580d-40dd-bdb0-010036a3d8b6.html</ref>\nRadio Vaticana, Radio Classica, and Radio Popolare.\n\n==Recordings==\n\n\u2022 2019 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - \"Verdi Fantasias\", Concerto Classics\n\n\u2022 2018 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - Saint Sa\u00ebns Violin Sonatas, Warner Classics\n\n\u2022 2017 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - Poulenc / Ravel / Stravinsky / Prokofiev, Warner Classics\n\n\u2022 2016 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - \"Italian Soul - Anima italiana\", Sony Classical\n\n\u2022 2013 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - \"Verdi Fantasias\", Sony Classical\n\n\u2022 2011 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Stefania Mormone (piano) - Saint-Sa\u00ebns / Wieniawski / Grieg / Ponce / Elgar / Debussy, Amadeus\n\n==Instruments==\n\n\nAlessio Bidoli plays one of the violins made by his grandfather, Dante Regazzoni, a Lombard violin-maker whose workshop is now part of the Museo della Liuteria (MUSA) at the Accademia Nazionle di Santa Cecilia, Rome. <ref>https://amadeusmagazine.it/rubrica-news/in-un-cd-tutto-saint-saens-per-violino-e-pianoforte-con-il-duo-bidoli-canino/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.alessiobidoli.com Alessio Bidoli official website]\n\n\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bidoli, Alessio}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Milan]]\n[[Category:Italian classical violinists]]\n[[Category:Male violinists]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical violinists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male musicians]]\n\n\n{{violinist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{pp-protected|reason=Persistent [[WP:Disruptive editing|disruptive editing]]|small=yes}}\n{{COI|date=April 2020}}\n{{Notability|Music|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name        = Alessio Bidoli\n| image = Alessio Bidoli e Bruno Canino (Ivrea SMC records studio).jpg\n| alt       = \n| caption      = \n| image_size     = \n| background     = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name     = \n| alias       = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|08|18}}\n| birth_place    = \n| death_date     = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|1986|08|18}} (death date then birth) -->\n| origin       = \n| instrument     = Violin\n| genre       = [[Classical music|Classical]]\n| occupation     = \n| years_active    = \n| label       = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website      = {{url|http://www.alessiobidoli.com}}\n}}\n'''Alessio Bidoli''' (born 1986) is a Italian violinist.  <ref>https://www.7giorni.info/cultura/peschiera-borromeo/il-talento-peschierese-alessio-bidoli-si-esibira-al-teatro-cinema-de-sica.html</ref>\n\n==Biography==\n\n===Musical education===\nShe was introduced to music with piano studies at age 6; in the following years, he began studying the violin. Even in the early years, he began to perform publicly as a soloist, participating in and winning numerous national competitions. <ref>https://www.universalmusic.it/musica-classica/artista/alessio-bidoli_33761664456/ </ref> At age 21, she was admitted at the Haute Ecole de Musique de Lausanne and Mozarteum (Salzburg) under Pierre Amoyal , and then the [[Accademia Musicale Chigiana]] in Siena, where she was trained by Master [[Salvatore Accardo]].<ref>http://www.mitosettembremusica.it/sites/default/files/2019-05/30_alessio_bidoli_san_fedele_scheda_web_print.pdf</ref>\nAt age 20, he graduated from the Verdi Conservatory in [[Milan]] with highest marks and honors. He then received a specialization diploma for violin from the International Piano Academy \"Incontri col Maestro\" in Imola.<ref>https://www.mywhere.it/70627/alessio-bidoli-chamber-works-nino-rota.html</ref>\n\n===Career===\n\n\nHe performed and collaborated with international musicians such as [[Bruno Canino]], [[Pierre Amoyal]], Irene Veneziano,Massimo Mercelli and many others. <ref>https://open.spotify.com/artist/1ojJIJOWiOBM7BS2gAc3Ld</ref>\nHe has featured with [[Vittorio Sgarbi]] in the theatre project Il Fin la Maraviglia, an account of the Baroque age via images and sounds, which was performed at the theatre in Chiasso (Switzerland) in 2015.<ref>https://luganoeventi.ch/it/eventi/25985/il-fin-la-maraviglia</ref>\nIn April 2009, he was struck down by a viral infection that led to his becoming tetraplegic, arising from Guillain-Barr\u00e9 Syndrome, but he succeeded in playing the violin again two years later, despite his medical prognosis<ref>https://www.corriere.it/buone-notizie/cards/natale-neurochirurgo-italiano-che-salva-bambini-kirgizi-5-storie-corriere/alessio-violino-nonno_principale.shtml</ref>\nBidoli has appeared as guest artist in radio broadcasts on Radio France, NDR Kultur, Radio Svizzera Italiana, RAI Radio 3<ref>https://www.raiplayradio.it/audio/2018/11/PRIMO--MOVIMENTO-5662aef6-580d-40dd-bdb0-010036a3d8b6.html</ref>\nRadio Vaticana, Radio Classica, and Radio Popolare.\n\n==Recordings==\n\n\u2022 2019 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - \"Verdi Fantasias\", Concerto Classics\n\n\u2022 2018 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - Saint Sa\u00ebns Violin Sonatas, Warner Classics\n\n\u2022 2017 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - Poulenc / Ravel / Stravinsky / Prokofiev, Warner Classics\n\n\u2022 2016 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - \"Italian Soul - Anima italiana\", Sony Classical\n\n\u2022 2013 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Bruno Canino (piano) - \"Verdi Fantasias\", Sony Classical\n\n\u2022 2011 Alessio Bidoli (violin) and Stefania Mormone (piano) - Saint-Sa\u00ebns / Wieniawski / Grieg / Ponce / Elgar / Debussy, Amadeus\n\n==Instruments==\n\n\nAlessio Bidoli plays one of the violins made by his grandfather, Dante Regazzoni, a Lombard violin-maker whose workshop is now part of the Museo della Liuteria (MUSA) at the Accademia Nazionle di Santa Cecilia, Rome. <ref>https://amadeusmagazine.it/rubrica-news/in-un-cd-tutto-saint-saens-per-violino-e-pianoforte-con-il-duo-bidoli-canino/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.alessiobidoli.com Alessio Bidoli official website]\n\n\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bidoli, Alessio}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Milan]]\n[[Category:Italian classical violinists]]\n[[Category:Male violinists]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical violinists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male musicians]]\n\n\n{{violinist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Dl2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "repair template damage; tidy", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alessio_Bidoli"}
